# safe-exec.allow.list — ERE patterns that rescue a command from a NON-critical
# deny match (REQ-08-01). One pattern per line; # comments and blank lines
# ignored. Matched case-insensitively against the whitespace-normalized command.
#
# Scope rules (decision 2026-06-11):
# - An allow match overrides only non-critical deny patterns.
# - Patterns listed in safe-exec.critical.list (reverse shells, rm -rf /,
#   curl|bash, disk overwrite, ...) can NEVER be rescued.
# - Every override is logged to .multica/safe-exec.log as ALLOW_OVERRIDE.
#
# Ships empty. Add narrow, project-specific rescues; keep them as specific as
# possible (anchor paths/remotes), e.g.:
#
#   ^git push --force-with-lease origin (feat|fix)/
#   ^rm -rf /tmp/build/
#   ^find \./node_modules .*-delete
